<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-11 00:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expos Closer Urbina To Undergo MRI  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- Montreal Expos closer Ugueth Urbina missed
Wednesday night's 8-0 loss to the Philadelphia Phillies after
feeling pain in his right elbow while warming up the previous
night.
</P>
<P>
   ''Last night, he threw a pitch and felt something,'' Expos
manager Felipe Alou said.
</P>
<P>
   Urbina, last year's NL saves leader with 41, told team officials
about the pain following the Expos' 3-2 win Tuesday night. X-rays
of the elbow were taken on Wednesday and an MRI will be performed
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   He struck out the side while recording his eighth save in his
last outing, Sunday at Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think he has pitched twice in the last 10 days,'' Alou said.
''He has been underpitched. He has 13 innings so far; that's very
low. And he has been very effective. He has 22 strikeouts in 13
innings, so the stuff has been there.''
</P>
<P>
   Urbina, 26, had bone chips removed from his right elbow in
December 1996 after experiencing pain while pitching in his native
Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
   The injury is the latest of a series that have plagued the
Expos' bullpen this season.
</P>
<P>
   Graeme Lloyd, signed as a free agent be to Montreal's set man,
hasn't pitched this season. He had arthroscopic surgery on his left
shoulder May 4 and won't return for at least three months.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Strickland, the Expos' current setup man, is on the
disabled list because of right shoulder tendinitis.
</P>
<P>
   ''We'll see what transpires with Ugie but the fact that right
now, we're not talking about pitching, we're talking about an MRI,
and we have the guy who was supposed to be our setup guy out, too,
so changes will have to take place,'' Alou said. ''Rearrangement of
the pitching staff will have to take place.''
</P>
<P>
   One option is moving staff ace Dustin Hermanson into the
closer's role.
</P>
<P>
   ''I love the job of closing but it's not the way that I wanted
to get a closing job,'' Hermanson said. ''Ugie's such a good,
aggressive pitcher. It's a big loss to the team if he is out for a
while, but we've got to do whatever we've got to do to win games.
And whatever they need me to do, I just want to win.''
</P>
<P>
   Acquired from Florida just before the beginning of the 1997
season, Hermanson was converted into a starter with Montreal. He
responded with a 14-11, 3.13 ERA season in 1998 and led the staff
with 34 starts last season, despite going 9-14 with a 4.20 ERA.
</P>
<P>
   Hermanson, who had no saves in 34 relief appearances with San
Diego from 1995-96, saved 21 games for Triple-A Las Vegas in 1996.
He has made 99 career starts, all with the Expos, and is 3-3 with a
4.81 ERA this season.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've always been groomed as a closer,'' Hermanson said.
''Plus, my mentality when I'm out there is a closer's mentality.
I'll do whatever the team wants me to do.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
