   Superior Court Judge Charles G. Ruben also ordered Berry to
perform 200 hours of community service.
</P>
<P>
   Berry was driving a rented sport utility vehicle that ran a red
light and collided with another car at a West Hollywood
intersection on Feb. 23, then drove off, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The other driver, Hetal Raythatha, suffered injuries including a
broken wrist and is suing the actress for unspecified damages.
Berry was treated for a cut on her forehead.
</P>
<P>
   Berry's attorney, Blair Berk, said prosecutors found no evidence
that the actress was under the influence of drugs or alcohol.
</P>
