<HEADLINE> Government Report Boosts Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mostly higher today as a report of a
slowdown in retail sales calmed investors who have been selling
stocks amid fears about rising interest rates.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 160.12 at 10,527.90.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Nasdaq composite
