<HEADLINE> DaimlerChrysler Hires GM Executive  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- DaimlerChrysler AG says it has hired
manufacturing executive Thomas LaSorda away from General Motors
Corp.
</P>
<P>
   LaSorda, a GM vice president for quality, was an architect of
its lean-manufacturing systems. He joins DaimlerChrysler as a
senior vice president for powertrain manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
   LaSorda replaces Carlos Lobo, who left to run New Venture Gear,
a joint venture of GM and DaimlerChrysler that makes engines and
transmissions, The Detroit News said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The Canadian-born LaSorda, 45, joined GM in 1977 and worked in a
variety of labor relations, manufacturing and quality-related
positions.
</P>
<P>
   He was a key member of the team that started up a new assembly
plant in Eisenach, Germany, for GM's Opel unit.
</P>
<P>
   The Eisenach plant's lean techniques are being applied in a
series of new GM factories going up around the world.
</P>
