</P>
<P>
   MANILA, Philippines (AP) -- A computer student sought by
investigators in the ''Love Bug'' virus case emerged from hiding
today to say he may have accidentally released the malicious
program that disrupted computer systems around the world. Onel A.
de Guzman declined to say whether he wrote the virus. The program
released last week sent a flood of e-mails with the subject line
''ILOVEYOU'' speeding through computer systems worldwide. Opening
the attachment destroyed saved files, and sent the virus along to
other addresses in the user's e-mail file.
