   Sharp Profits Jump on LCD Sales
</P>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese electronics maker Sharp Corp.'s group
profit surged by more than six times for the latest fiscal year as
sales of liquid crystal displays soared. The earnings growth
reported today follows two years of profit declines. Strong demand
for liquid crystal displays outstripped supply, creating shortages
and helping push prices higher. For the fiscal year ended March 31,
Sharp's earnings rose to 28.13 billion yen, or $256.4 million, from
4.63 billion yen the previous year. Demand for game machines and
cellular phones spurred sales of LCDs.
</P>
