that it earned $22 million, or 5 cents a share, in the quarter
ended April 26, compared with $56 million, or 11 cents a share, a
year ago. Sales for the quarter were $8.19 billion, up from $8.08
billion a year ago. Shares in Kmart fell [ to 7{.
