<HEADLINE> A's Demote Pitcher Prieto  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Ariel Prieto, ineffective in his only
start after the Oakland Athletics called him up from the minors,
was sent back to Sacramento of the Pacific Coast League on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The A's, who needed a second lefty in the bullpen, also promoted
left-hander Rich Sauveur from Sacramento.
</P>
<P>
   Prieto, a right-hander, was recalled from Sacramento on Monday
and started that night at Anaheim. He allowed five runs on 11 hits
in four innings, but was not involved in the decision as the A's
lost 9-8 to the Angels.
</P>
<P>
   Prieto was Oakland's first-round pick in the 1995 free-agent
draft and was Oakland's opening day starter in 1997. He missed all
of last season while recovering from elbow surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Sauveur was 2-0 with a save and a 3.90 ERA in 10 games, four of
them starts, for the Sacramento River Cats. The 36-year-old Sauveur
made his major league debut for Pittsburgh in 1986 and also has
played briefly for Montreal, the New York Mets, Kansas City and the
Chicago White Sox.
</P>
<P>
   His last major league appearance was on Aug. 20, 1996, for the
White Sox at Detroit.
</P>
