<HEADLINE> Cubs Place Grace on 15-Day DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago Cubs placed Mark Grace on the 15-day
disabled list Thursday with a strained left hamstring.
</P>
<P>
   The Cubs recalled first baseman Julio Zuleta to take his place.
The team also designated pitcher Andrew Lorraine for assignment and
called up Todd Van Poppel.
</P>
<P>
   Van Poppel went to the Cubs spring training camp as a non-roster
invitee. He has pitched in the majors with Oakland, Detroit, Texas
and Pittsburgh, going 22-37 with a 6.24 ERA in 135 big league
games. He was the A's first-round draft pick in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   He last pitched in a major league game Sept. 27, 1998, for the
Pirates at Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   Van Poppel was 3-4 with a 3.10 ERA in 10 games at Triple-A Iowa
and led the Pacific Coast League in strikeouts with 52.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm looking for any combination,'' Cubs manager Don Baylor
said of the addition of Van Poppel to the beleaguered bullpen.
</P>
<P>
   Grace suffered a strained left hamstring running to first base
in the ninth inning in Wednesday's 9-8 11-inning win over
Milwaukee. Grace was batting .294.
</P>
<P>
   Zuleta, who went 1-for-5 with an RBI in Thursday's 14-8 loss to
Milwaukee, was batting .302 with eight homers and 20 RBI in 28
games for Iowa.
</P>
<P>
   Lorraine was 1-2 with a 6.47 ERA in eight games.
</P>
