<HEADLINE> Yanks' Jeter Out With Pains  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Yankees shortstop Derek Jeter left Thursday
night's game against the Tampa Bay Devil Rays after the second
inning with an abdominal strain in his left side.
</P>
<P>
   Jeter appeared to injure himself with a leaping, twisting throw
to second on a ground ball hit by Vinny Castilla. He is listed as
day-to-day.
</P>
<P>
   Jeter has been mired in a slump and flied out in his only at-bat
to extend his hitless streak to 13 at bats over his last four
games.
</P>
