<HEADLINE> Wreck Kills 5 Teens in Miss.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOORHEAD, Miss. (AP) -- Three high school seniors days away from
graduation were among five teen-agers killed early Thursday when
their car went off a rural road and struck a utility pole.
</P>
<P>
   ''We don't know exactly what happened but we are working on
it,'' Sheriff Ned Holder said. ''This is the worst I've ever had to
deal with in my four terms as sheriff.''
</P>
<P>
   The three seniors, Colby Donahoo and Chris McCoy, both 18, and
JoAnna Smithhart, 17, attended Indianola Academy, a 477-student
private school that lost another member of its graduating class in
an October car accident.
</P>
<P>
   Jonathan Lute Zepponi, 19, an academy graduate who was attending
nearby Mississippi Delta Community College, and Jennifer Lynn
Alberson, 19, who attended the school last semester, also died.
</P>
<P>
   The young people ''were loved by their teachers and classmates
and the entire community will feel their loss,'' said Homer Burns,
Indianola Academy's headmaster.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have to say the families here are so close, our church
family and family friends,'' said the Rev. Anthony Quyet, who was
assisting Zepponi's family. ''They are very supportive of this
family in their time of need. This is really so hard to cope with,
to understand something of this magnitude.''
</P>
</TEXT>
