<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-11 23:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Dead, 2 Hurt in Hotel Shooting  </HEADLINE>
By ELISA BONGIOVANNI
<TEXT>
<P>
   MESA, Ariz. (AP) -- A gunfight in the hallway of a hotel Thursday
killed one person and wounded two others, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators believe the three people were the only ones
involved in the shooting, said police Sgt. Earle Lloyd. Two weapons
were found at the scene, and police were trying to determine a
motive.
</P>
<P>
   The victims, believed to be in their thirties, were found on the
third floor of the Fairfield Inn near U.S. 60, said Mary Cameli, a
spokeswoman for the Mesa Fire Department.
</P>
<P>
   A woman shot in the chest and a man shot in the face were taken
to a hospital where she was listed in critical condition and he had
non-life threatening injuries, Lloyd said.
</P>
<P>
   The hotel had been 90 percent occupied Wednesday night, though
most guests had likely checked out by the time the shootings
occurred Thursday morning, said Michael Owen, manager for Fairfield
Inns.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm in shock,'' Owen said. ''This is really bad. Nothing like
this has ever happened at any of the hotels I've worked at.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
