<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-11 23:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Imprisoned Kidnapper's Son Abducted  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Authorities confirmed on Thursday that the
10-year-old son of an imprisoned kidnapper had been abducted.
</P>
<P>
   Carlos Arizmendi Suarez, son of Aurelio Arizmendi, was freed and
five suspects were detained Thursday in connection with the boy's
kidnapping, authorities from the Mexican Attorney General's office
said.
</P>
<P>
   Aurelio Arizmendi is imprisoned for kidnapping and mutilating
some of his victims. His wife, Adriana Suarez Arista, was charged
Wednesday with organized crime and owning illegally obtained
property.
</P>
<P>
   When Suarez was arrested on Sunday she first told authorities
her son had been kidnapped.
</P>
<P>
   The Arizmendi kidnapping band, headed by Daniel Arizmendi,
developed a reputation for cutting off the ears of some of its
victims and sending them to the families to pressure them for
ransom.
</P>
<P>
   The Arizmendi brothers were detained in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Carlos' kidnappers had asked for $2 million for the child,
authorities said.
</P>
</TEXT>
